'''''Dux''''' (plural ''Duces'') is [[Latin]] for "leader". The term is primarily used in a military context.

==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
LL  dux, leader

===Noun===
'''dux''' (''plural:'' '''duces''')
# (Scotland, New Zealand, Australia) the top student in a class.
#  a high-ranking commander in the Roman army, responsible for more than one legion.



